Settlement of claims.

âThe System is hereby empowered to adopt rules and regulations to expedite the settlement of claims under the provisions of this Act. If the money is payable to the estate of a deceased person, the System shall pay the same to such person or persons as it may ascertain to be lawfully entitled thereto in accordance with existing laws on succession. If the money is payable to a minor, payment shall be made by the System to such person or persons as it may consider to be best qualified to take care and dispose of the minor's property for his benefit."
